value.0: A feeding pit for the Qion Slugs reside here, with corpses scattered about; most had been partially digested, with others in varying stages of decomposition. Marks indicate that other bodies had pulled by the slugs into a warren of tunnels...

A thick layer of slime and mucus appears to have coated and trapped either a sacrificed victim of the Byysk or one of their hunted offerings of meat and flesh. Closer inspection reveals tiny larvae infesting the gruesome coating...

The Qion Hive's tunnels stretch for leagues endlessly onwards, perhaps eventually coming out to the surface of Hutlar; but here they begin to climb and drop, or become narrower at points, beyond the ability of any but the younger Qion Slugs to traverse...
The worm tunnels stretch for leagues onwards...
